  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to sign in.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature, User Experience\r\n\r\n*Summary*: On the Sign In screen, I type my password and press the Sign in button... and nothing happens for three seconds. This is confusing because I wonder if I pressed the button correctly.  \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhen I tap the Sign In button, the app should show an activity indicator.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nWhen I tap the Sign In button, the keyboard dismisses but nothing else happens for three seconds until the screen changes.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nForce Quit the app. Open the app. Tap your username. Type your password. Tap the Sign In button.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nI think the easy way to fix this would be to replace the words, \"Sign In\", inside the button, with an activity indicator spinner while the app is authenticating the user.\r\n\r\n![img_0204-2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5604/25883434/8a4cf912-34ff-11e7-8a2b-bfa4e0aec92c.png)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.7d64\r\n* Operating System: iOS, iPhone 6 Plus",
